   "source": [
    "# Missing Values and Duplicate Data\n",
    "\n",
    "## A Practical Guide with Real-World Examples\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we will explore two of the most common data quality issues: missing values and duplicate records. We'll create sample data, detect issues, and apply cleaning techniques."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import required libraries\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set display options\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_rows', 50)\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.width', None)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Libraries imported successfully!\")\n",
    "print(f\"Pandas version: {pd.__version__}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Introduction to Missing Values\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing values occur when information that should exist in a dataset is absent. A field may be empty because:\n",
    "- The information was never collected\n",
    "- The user refused to provide it\n",
    "- The sensor failed\n",
    "- The value was deleted accidentally\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Insight:** Real-world datasets are almost never complete. Data preprocessing is a critical stage because algorithms assume structured and available information."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a sample dataset with missing values\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create base data\n",
    "n_employees = 100\n",
    "employee_ids = range(1001, 1001 + n_employees)\n",
    "names = [f\"Employee_{i}\" for i in range(1, n_employees + 1)]\n",
    "ages = np.random.normal(35, 10, n_employees).astype(int)\n",
    "salaries = np.random.normal(50000, 15000, n_employees).astype(int)\n",
    "departments = np.random.choice(['HR', 'IT', 'Finance', 'Marketing', 'Sales'], n_employees)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_missing = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'employee_id': employee_ids,\n",
    "    'name': names,\n",
    "    'age': ages,\n",
    "    'salary': salaries,\n",
    "    'department': departments\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Introduce missing values\n",
    "missing_age_idx = np.random.choice(df_missing.index, 15, replace=False)\n",
    "df_missing.loc[missing_age_idx, 'age'] = np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "missing_salary_idx = np.random.choice(df_missing.index, 12, replace=False)\n",
    "df_missing.loc[missing_salary_idx, 'salary'] = np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "missing_dept_idx = np.random.choice(df_missing.index, 8, replace=False)\n",
    "df_missing.loc[missing_dept_idx, 'department'] = np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Sample Dataset with Missing Values\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape: {df_missing.shape}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 15 rows:\")\n",
    "df_missing.head(15)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check missing values count\n",
    "print(\"MISSING VALUES COUNT\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 30)\n",
    "missing_counts = df_missing.isnull().sum()\n",
    "missing_percentages = (df_missing.isnull().sum() / len(df_missing)) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "missing_summary = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Column': missing_counts.index,\n",
    "    'Missing Count': missing_counts.values,\n",
    "    'Missing Percentage': missing_percentages.values\n",
    "})\n",
    "print(missing_summary.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize missing values\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(df_missing.isnull(), yticklabels=False, cbar=True, cmap='viridis')\n",
    "plt.title('Missing Values Heatmap', fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Columns')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Rows')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Real-World Nature of Missing Data\n",
    "\n",
    "A common misconception is that machine learning mainly involves downloading datasets and training models immediately.\n",
    "\n",
    "In reality, real-world systems require multiple stages:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Stage | Description |\n",
    "|-------|-------------|\n",
    "| Attribute Identification | Deciding what to collect |\n",
    "| Data Collection | Sensors, forms, APIs, surveys |\n",
    "| Data Storage | Structuring into databases |\n",
    "| Data Cleaning | Removing inconsistencies |\n",
    "| Data Preprocessing | Handling errors and gaps |\n",
    "| ML Modeling | Applying algorithms |\n",
    "\n",
    "**The difficult part is usually not model training. It is collecting usable data.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Causes of Missing Values\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing values arise for several practical reasons:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Cause | Example |\n",
    "|-------|---------|\n",
    "| Sensor Failure | Temperature sensor malfunction |\n",
    "| User Refusal | User hides salary or age |\n",
    "| Data Deletion | Corrupted database rows |\n",
    "| Human Error | Field skipped accidentally |\n",
    "| Non-applicable Data | Child income field |\n",
    "| System Failure | Incomplete API response |\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Name | Age | Salary |\n",
    "|------|-----|--------|\n",
    "| Ravi | 32 | 900000 |\n",
    "| Anita | NULL | 700000 |\n",
    "\n",
    "The missing age value may exist because the user refused disclosure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulate different causes of missing values\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "survey_data = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'user_id': range(1, 51),\n",
    "    'age': np.random.randint(18, 80, 50),\n",
    "    'income': np.random.randint(20000, 150000, 50),\n",
    "    'satisfaction_score': np.random.randint(1, 6, 50),\n",
    "    'feedback_text': [f\"Comment_{i}\" for i in range(1, 51)]\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cause 1: User refusal (sensitive question - income)\n",
    "refusal_idx = np.random.choice(survey_data.index, 8, replace=False)\n",
    "survey_data.loc[refusal_idx, 'income'] = np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cause 2: Human error (skipped age field)\n",
    "error_idx = np.random.choice(survey_data.index, 5, replace=False)\n",
    "survey_data.loc[error_idx, 'age'] = np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cause 3: Non-applicable (keep as is)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"SURVEY DATA WITH MISSING VALUES FROM DIFFERENT CAUSES\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(f\"Missing income (user refusal): {survey_data['income'].isnull().sum()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Missing age (human error): {survey_data['age'].isnull().sum()}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nSample rows:\")\n",
    "survey_data.head(15)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Disguised Missing Values\n",
    "\n",
    "One of the most dangerous preprocessing problems is **disguised missing data**.\n",
    "\n",
    "Normally, missing values are easy to detect because fields appear empty: NULL or NA.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, disguised missing values contain **fake placeholder entries** instead of empty cells.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "A website may force users to select a birth date before submission. If users do not want to reveal their actual DOB, they leave the default value unchanged.\n",
    "\n",
    "The system now stores a fake but syntactically valid value.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hidden Problem:** Missing Information = Fake Placeholder Value"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create dataset with disguised missing values\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Real data\n",
    "real_ages = np.random.randint(18, 80, 100)\n",
    "real_incomes = np.random.randint(25000, 200000, 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create disguised missing values\n",
    "disguised_ages = real_ages.copy()\n",
    "disguised_incomes = real_incomes.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Default placeholder values (disguised missing)\n",
    "default_age = 0\n",
    "default_income = -1\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replace some values with disguised missing\n",
    "disguised_age_idx = np.random.choice(range(100), 20, replace=False)\n",
    "disguised_ages[disguised_age_idx] = default_age\n",
    "\n",
    "disguised_income_idx = np.random.choice(range(100), 15, replace=False)\n",
    "disguised_incomes[disguised_income_idx] = default_income\n",
    "\n",
    "df_disguised = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'customer_id': range(1, 101),\n",
    "    'age': disguised_ages,\n",
    "    'income': disguised_incomes\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"DATASET WITH DISGUISED MISSING VALUES\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "print(\"Note: age=0 and income=-1 are disguised missing values\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nStatistics (shows disguised missing as real values):\")\n",
    "print(df_disguised.describe())\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 20 rows:\")\n",
    "df_disguised.head(20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Why Disguised Missing Data is Dangerous\n",
    "\n",
    "Disguised missing values are difficult because traditional null-checking methods fail.\n",
    "\n",
    "A standard preprocessing check might search for:\n",
    "- NULL\n",
    "- NA\n",
    "- Empty strings\n",
    "\n",
    "But disguised missing data already contains values.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Example:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| User | DOB |\n",
    "|------|-----|\n",
    "| A | 01-01-1990 |\n",
    "| B | 01-01-1990 |\n",
    "| C | 01-01-1990 |\n",
    "\n",
    "The system may incorrectly conclude that many users were born on the same date. This introduces statistical distortion."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate the danger of disguised missing values\n",
    "print(\"THE DANGER OF DISGUISED MISSING VALUES\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 55)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate statistics with disguised missing\n",
    "print(\"\\n1. Statistics INCLUDING disguised missing values:\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Mean age: {df_disguised['age'].mean():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Min age: {df_disguised['age'].min()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Age distribution: {df_disguised['age'].value_counts().head()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert disguised missing to true missing\n",
    "df_fixed = df_disguised.copy()\n",
    "df_fixed['age'] = df_fixed['age'].replace(0, np.nan)\n",
    "df_fixed['income'] = df_fixed['income'].replace(-1, np.nan)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n2. Statistics EXCLUDING disguised missing (after conversion to NaN):\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Mean age: {df_fixed['age'].mean():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Missing ages: {df_fixed['age'].isnull().sum()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Missing incomes: {df_fixed['income'].isnull().sum()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 55)\n",
    "print(\"CONCLUSION: Disguised missing values distort statistics and\")\n",
    "print(\"go undetected by standard missing value checks!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Handling Missing Values\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing values are handled using multiple strategies depending on the severity and context:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method | Description |\n",
    "|--------|-------------|\n",
    "| Ignore Rows | Remove incomplete observations |\n",
    "| Manual Filling | Human correction |\n",
    "| Global Constant | Fill using fixed value |\n",
    "| Mean Imputation | Replace using average |\n",
    "| Median Imputation | Replace using median |\n",
    "| Mode Imputation | Replace using most frequent |\n",
    "| Forward Fill | Use previous value |\n",
    "| Backward Fill | Use next value |\n",
    "| Inference-Based | Predict missing values |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Mean Imputation Formula:\n",
    "\n",
    "x_bar = (1/n) * sum(x_i)\n",
    "\n",
    "If mean salary is 55000, then NULL may be replaced with 55000."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate different imputation methods\n",
    "print(\"MISSING VALUE IMPUTATION METHODS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a copy for each method\n",
    "df_mean = df_missing.copy()\n",
    "df_median = df_missing.copy()\n",
    "df_mode = df_missing.copy()\n",
    "df_forward = df_missing.copy()\n",
    "df_drop = df_missing.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 1: Mean Imputation\n",
    "age_mean = df_mean['age'].mean()\n",
    "salary_mean = df_mean['salary'].mean()\n",
    "df_mean['age'] = df_mean['age'].fillna(age_mean)\n",
    "df_mean['salary'] = df_mean['salary'].fillna(salary_mean)\n",
    "print(f\"\\n1. Mean Imputation:\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Age mean: {age_mean:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Salary mean: {salary_mean:.2f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 2: Median Imputation\n",
    "age_median = df_median['age'].median()\n",
    "salary_median = df_median['salary'].median()\n",
    "df_median['age'] = df_median['age'].fillna(age_median)\n",
    "df_median['salary'] = df_median['salary'].fillna(salary_median)\n",
    "print(f\"\\n2. Median Imputation:\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Age median: {age_median:.0f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Salary median: {salary_median:.0f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 3: Mode Imputation (for categorical)\n",
    "dept_mode = df_mode['department'].mode()[0]\n",
    "df_mode['department'] = df_mode['department'].fillna(dept_mode)\n",
    "print(f\"\\n3. Mode Imputation:\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Department mode: {dept_mode}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 4: Forward Fill\n",
    "df_forward['age'] = df_forward['age'].fillna(method='ffill')\n",
    "print(f\"\\n4. Forward Fill: Used previous age values\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 5: Drop rows with missing values\n",
    "df_drop = df_drop.dropna()\n",
    "print(f\"\\n5. Drop Missing Rows: {len(df_missing)} -> {len(df_drop)} rows\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize imputation results\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Original distribution\n",
    "original_age = df_missing['age'].dropna()\n",
