    "## 10. Entity Identification Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "A major challenge in duplicate handling is **entity identification**.\n",
    "\n",
    "The system must determine whether two records represent the same real-world entity.\n",
    "\n",
    "This becomes difficult because names, addresses, and identifiers may differ slightly.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Example:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Record A | Record B |\n",
    "|----------|----------|\n",
    "| Heman R | Heman Rathore |\n",
    "\n",
    "Humans easily infer similarity. Machines require probabilistic matching algorithms.\n",
    "\n",
    "This problem is also called:\n",
    "- Record linkage\n",
    "- Entity resolution\n",
    "- Deduplication\n",
    "\n",
    "The goal is: P(A = B) - estimating whether two records belong to the same entity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate simple entity matching\n",
    "from difflib import SequenceMatcher\n",
    "\n",
    "def similarity_ratio(a, b):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate string similarity ratio\"\"\"\n",
    "    return SequenceMatcher(None, a.lower(), b.lower()).ratio()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"ENTITY RESOLUTION USING STRING SIMILARITY\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "\n",
    "test_pairs = [\n",
    "    (\"Hemant Rathore\", \"H. Rathore\"),\n",
    "    (\"Priya Singh\", \"Priya S.\"),\n",
    "    (\"Rajesh Kumar\", \"R. Kumar\"),\n",
    "    (\"Amit Patel\", \"Patel Amit\"),\n",
    "    (\"Suresh Reddy\", \"S. Reddy\")\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nName Similarity Scores:\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 40)\n",
    "for name1, name2 in test_pairs:\n",
    "    score = similarity_ratio(name1, name2)\n",
    "    print(f\"'{name1}' vs '{name2}': {score:.2%}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  {'-> MATCH (likely same person)' if score > 0.6 else '-> NO MATCH (different persons)'}\")\n",
    "    print()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
