   "source": [
    "## 11. Detecting Duplicate Records\n",
    "\n",
    "Duplicate detection can be performed using multiple approaches:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Method | Purpose |\n",
    "|--------|---------|\n",
    "| Correlation Analysis | Detect similarity patterns |\n",
    "| Entity Matching | Compare identities |\n",
    "| Rule-Based Systems | Exact or fuzzy matching |\n",
    "| Manual Review | Human validation |\n",
    "\n",
    "The challenge is balancing false positives vs false negatives.\n",
    "\n",
    "Aggressive deduplication may accidentally remove legitimate records."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Demonstrate duplicate detection methods\n",
    "print(\"DUPLICATE DETECTION METHODS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 40)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 1: Exact duplicate detection\n",
    "exact_duplicates = customers_with_dup[customers_with_dup.duplicated(keep=False)]\n",
    "print(f\"\\n1. Exact duplicates found: {len(exact_duplicates)}\")\n",
    "if len(exact_duplicates) > 0:\n",
    "    print(exact_duplicates)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 2: Duplicate based on specific columns\n",
    "subset_duplicates = customers_with_dup[customers_with_dup.duplicated(subset=['name', 'city'], keep=False)]\n",
    "print(f\"\\n2. Duplicates based on name + city: {len(subset_duplicates)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 3: Remove duplicates\n",
    "customers_deduped = customers_with_dup.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "print(f\"\\n3. After removing exact duplicates: {len(customers_with_dup)} -> {len(customers_deduped)} rows\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Method 4: Keep first occurrence\n",
    "customers_first = customers_with_dup.drop_duplicates(keep='first')\n",
    "print(f\"4. After keeping first occurrence: {len(customers_first)} rows\")"
   ]
